detaileddescription.para:
adds given object at the end of children (recognized or not); returns false if it was already child of this, of if given pointer is empty; child object will always report this as parent after the call; 

recognizedChild



if set to false then child object will be excluded from children() and it will be stored by weak_ptr Generated from method MR::RadiusMeasurementObject::addChild. Parameter _this can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter recognizedChild has a default argument: true, pass a null pointer to use it.
